# Frontend stack

Next.js 15 В· React 19 В· TypeScript 5 В· Tailwind CSS v4 В· Radix UI В· App Router
State: Zustand (UI only) В· Forms: React Hook Form + Zod
Auth: Django JWT in **httpOnly cookies** (dj-rest-auth / SimpleJWT). Browser: `lib/api/client.ts` (refresh + session events). RSC: `serverFetchJson` + `lib/api/auth/server.ts` for `auth()`. Payments: Stripe.js Elements
Icons: React Icons / Lucide React В· Images: Cloudinary (signed uploads)

# The most important rule вЂ” where things live

```
app/           в†’ ONLY routing files: page.tsx, layout.tsx, loading.tsx, error.tsx, not-found.tsx
features/      в†’ ALL components organized by domain
components/    в†’ ONLY truly shared UI (used in 3+ features)
lib/api/       в†’ ALL fetch calls to Django API
store/         в†’ Zustand UI state only
```

**There are NO `_components` folders inside `app/`.** That was the main problem in the old project. If a component exists, it goes in `features/{domain}/components/`, not next to its page.

