# Server Components vs Client Components вЂ” the core rule

**Every component is a Server Component by default.**
Add `'use client'` ONLY when the component needs: browser events, useState, useEffect, browser APIs.

```typescript
// app/catalogo/page.tsx вЂ” Server Component (no 'use client')
// Can fetch data directly, has access to cookies/headers
import { getProducts } from "@/lib/api/products"
import { ProductGrid } from "@/features/catalog/components/ProductGrid"

export default async function CatalogPage({ searchParams }) {
  const products = await getProducts(searchParams)  // server-side fetch
  return <ProductGrid products={products} />
}

// features/catalog/components/FilterSheet.tsx вЂ” Client Component
"use client"  // needs state for open/close, user interaction
import { useState } from "react"

export function FilterSheet() {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false)
  ...
}
```

**Rule:** if you need `useState`, `useEffect`, `onClick`, `onChange` в†’ `'use client'`.
If you only render data в†’ Server Component, no directive needed.

# Special files вЂ” use them, don't skip them

```typescript
// app/(site)/(public)/catalogo/loading.tsx вЂ” shown while page.tsx fetches
export default function CatalogLoading() {
  return <ProductGridSkeleton />
}

// app/(site)/(public)/catalogo/error.tsx вЂ” shown on fetch error
"use client"
export default function CatalogError({ error, reset }) {
  return <ErrorState message="No pudimos cargar los productos." onRetry={reset} />
}

// app/not-found.tsx вЂ” shown on 404
export default function NotFound() {
  return <div>PГЎgina no encontrada</div>
}
```

Every route that fetches data MUST have a `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx`.

# Images вЂ” always next/image, never <img>

```typescript
// CORRECT вЂ” next/image handles optimization, lazy loading, WebP conversion
import Image from "next/image"

<Image
  src={product.image_url}
  alt={product.name}
  width={400}
  height={400}
  className="object-cover rounded-lg"
/>

// WRONG вЂ” raw <img> tag
<img src={product.image_url} alt={product.name} />
```

For Cloudinary images use the `fill` prop with a relative container:
```typescript
<div className="relative aspect-square">
  <Image src={cloudinaryUrl} alt={name} fill className="object-cover" />
</div>
```

# Metadata and SEO вЂ” always export generateMetadata

```typescript
// app/(site)/(public)/product/[slug]/page.tsx
import type { Metadata } from "next"
import { getProduct } from "@/lib/api/products"

export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const product = await getProduct(params.slug)
  return {
    title: `${product.name} | LSB Shop`,
    description: product.description,
    openGraph: {
      images: [product.image_url],
    },
  }
}
```

All public pages (catalog, product detail, home) must export `generateMetadata`.

# API client вЂ” contexts and helpers

Auth uses **JWT in httpOnly cookies** set by Django (`dj-rest-auth`). Do **not** add `Authorization: Bearer` headers from the frontend for normal API calls; rely on `credentials: "include"` via `client.ts` / forwarded cookies via `server-django.ts`.

```typescript
// в”Ђв”Ђ 1. CLIENT-SIDE (and any code running in the browser) в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
// lib/api/client.ts в†’ apiGet, apiPost, apiPatch, apiDelete (wrap apiFetch: refresh, errors)
// Use for: Client Components, hooks, cart sync, checkout client steps
import { apiGet } from "@/lib/api/client"

// в”Ђв”Ђ 2. PUBLIC Server Components (no user session required) в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
// Still OK to use apiGet from a Server Component ONLY when the endpoint is public
// and you are not relying on browser-only refresh behavior.

// в”Ђв”Ђ 3. SERVER-ONLY reads/mutations that need the user's Django session в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
// lib/api/server-django.ts в†’ serverFetchJson / serverMutationJson
// Forwards `Cookie` from next/headers вЂ” required for account/checkout pages as RSC
import { serverFetchJson } from "@/lib/api/server-django"

// в”Ђв”Ђ 4. RSC вЂњcurrent userвЂќ guard в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
// lib/api/auth/server.ts в†’ auth() cached per request вЂ” import ONLY from here
import { auth } from "@/lib/api/auth/server"

// в”Ђв”Ђ 5. ROUTE HANDLERS (app/api/вЂ¦/route.ts) в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
// Cuando hace falta secretos en servidor o firmas: p. ej. `sign-cloudinary-params`, `cloudinary/delete`, bГєsqueda/load-more
```

**Decision rule:**
- Default browser calls в†’ `client.ts`
- RSC / layout needs session-backed Django JSON в†’ `serverFetchJson` (often via `lib/api/{domain}/server.ts`)
- Same DRF payload mapped in two places в†’ **one** `mappers.ts` used by both `index.ts` and `server.ts`
- `auth()` in RSC в†’ `@/lib/api/auth/server` only
- Mutations from Server Actions в†’ `serverMutationJson` + `"use server"`

See `docs/FRONTEND_API.md` for the canonical write-up.

# DRY вЂ” duplicate code in the API layer (when it is worth it)

When editing `lib/api/**` or DRF-related types, also follow `.cursor/rules/frontend-api-dry.mdc` (same globs cover `lib/api` and `types/`).

**Always consolidate when:**

- The same **DRF response** is mapped to app types in **more than one** file в†’ **one** `mappers.ts` (or shared types + one mapper module).
- **`index.ts` + `server.ts`** exist for the same domain and both touch the same JSON shape в†’ shared mappers, not copy-paste.

**Do not over-abstract when:**

- The mapping exists in **one** place only and there is no second consumer.
- Extraction would make the data flow harder to follow for a one-off endpoint.

**Quick check before committing API work:** search the folder for repeated `_*` field assignments from the same API response.

For **shared fields between domain interfaces** in `types/*.ts` (bases + `extends`), see section **6** in `.cursor/rules/frontend-api-dry.mdc` вЂ” same idea as DRY for API mappers, applied to TypeScript models only where semantics align (not for raw DRF JSON types).

# Naming conventions

- Components: `PascalCase` в†’ `ProductCard.tsx`
- Hooks: `camelCase` with `use` prefix в†’ `useCartActions.ts`
- Store: `camelCase` with `Store` suffix в†’ `useUIStore.ts`
- Utils: `camelCase` В· Types: `PascalCase` В· Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Route segments: `kebab-case`

# Forms вЂ” React Hook Form + Zod always

```typescript
const loginSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email("Email invГЎlido"),
  password: z.string().min(8, "MГ­nimo 8 caracteres"),
})
type LoginForm = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>

// Submit button disabled while pending, field errors shown below each input
// Never use uncontrolled inputs for forms
```

# UI rules

- Loading: always show `<ComponentSkeleton />` while fetching
- Error: always show `<ErrorState message="..." onRetry={refetch} />`
- Empty: always show `<EmptyState title="..." description="..." />`
- Toasts: always human language вЂ” never `toast.error(error.message)`
- Images: always `next/image` вЂ” never `<img>`
